your team. Yeah, I think the general state of football is in a really good spot. Last year,

00:56:34.479 --> 00:56:41.919
we had the lowest margin of victory since, I think, 1932. The game itself, a lot of the sort

00:56:41.919 --> 00:56:46.399
of analytic driven trends, and I saw a couple of questions in the chat about these. Teams are going

00:56:46.560 --> 00:56:51.760
forward and forth down more often. Teams are coming up with more creative offenses. All of that has led to a more entertaining football. I mean, I don't think anybody has ever turned on a football game and they're like, oh, this is going to be awesome. I can't wait to see this punt play.

00:56:51.760 --> 00:56:59.360
So, in general, like the things that are happening to football is making it more exciting to watch,

00:56:59.360 --> 00:57:04.320
and I do think that that's created a, you know, it's always been an entertaining product, but it's

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:09.760
it's really exciting to watch, and I think that that's one of the things that we're really excited about this year.

00:57:09.760 --> 00:57:14.800
is making it more exciting to watch, and I do think that that's created a, you know, it's always

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:20.000
been an entertaining product, but it's really at its peak. So, I think, honestly, the sort of

00:57:20.000 --> 00:57:26.560
trend for the game itself is in good shape, and, you know, that I think continues to make

00:57:26.560 --> 00:57:31.439
me excited about this season. It's always the case that because you have a small sample

00:57:31.439 --> 00:57:36.560
